      "content": "but if you look at the actual outcome, it seems like the 'humanitarian' side didn't even matter in the end because the whole country fell apart. doesn't that make the R2P argument pretty much a failure in practice? like, if the result is just more chaos, was there ever a legitimate strategic reason to do it?",
